<div class="container">
    <p>I developed this tool after i couldn&#39t find a good web base application for managing and displaying pictures that i
        regularly would use for my gesture drawing practice sessions. The idea was to have a simple and intuitive
        interface that would allow me to quickly load a set of images, display them in a grid format, and then cycle
        through them with a simple click or tap. The app also allows for easy navigation between images, making it
        perfect for quick reference during drawing sessions with usefull functions to adapt the to the user preference.
    </p>

    <p>As i didn&#39t require a cloud storage (all the images are always local to the user device), tracking or accounts,
        it made easy the choice to go purely frontend, with React and vanilla Javascript as the main tools for it&#39s development.
    </p>

    <p>At the moments the app it&#39s feature complete, with some quality of life and small functions coming in the future.</p>


